DataElement.preferredName: Jebsen-Taylor Hand Function Test NonDominant Hand Score
DataElement.preferredDefinition: Numeric value to represent the nondominant hand score on the Jebsen-Taylor Hand Function Test, a seven part test that evaluates a broad range of hand functions used in daily activities using common items such as cans, paper clips, and pencils.
